<i>The mirror stares you in the face</i>

54:19.684 --> 54:22.881
<i>And says, "Baby... it don't work"</i>

54:23.054 --> 54:26.581
<i>You say your prayers</i>
<i>Though you don't care</i>

54:26.758 --> 54:29.727
<i>You dance and shake the hurt</i>

54:29.894 --> 54:31.259
<i>Dance!</i>

54:31.429 --> 54:32.521
Mumble!

54:32.697 --> 54:36.895
<i>Boogie wonderland</i>

54:37.068 --> 54:38.968
<i>Dance, dance, dance</i>

54:39.137 --> 54:40.297
<i>Mumble</i>

54:40.472 --> 54:42.599
<i>Boogie wonderland</i>

54:42.774 --> 54:45.299
<i>Check it out, check it out</i>
<i>Check it out, check it out</i>

54:47.312 --> 54:48.870
<i>My brothers</i>

54:56.222 --> 54:59.123
<i>You look so beautiful to me, baby</i>

55:08.668 --> 55:10.363
- Mumble.
- Hey, Miss Viola.

55:10.536 --> 55:16.168
<i>- All the love in the world can't be gone</i>
<i>- Mumble!</i>

55:16.342 --> 55:21.302
<i>- All the need to be loved can't be wrong</i>
<i>- Mumble!</i>

55:21.480 --> 55:23.038
Disgraceful!

55:24.717 --> 55:26.446
Who do they think they are?

55:26.619 --> 55:30.214
Where is Noah?
This is getting out of hand.

55:30.589 --> 55:32.181
Go!

55:36.462 --> 55:38.862
Hey, Memphis. It's your boy, Mumble.

55:39.432 --> 55:42.265
- Mumble?
- Mumble?

55:42.435 --> 55:45.927
No, no. No, it's "Mambo." O!

55:46.105 --> 55:49.563
Baby. They're saying, "Mumble."

56:10.963 --> 56:11.987
Boogie!

56:12.264 --> 56:13.458
Behold, Noah, look!

56:13.632 --> 56:19.628
This was an omen from the start
and now we have this uprising.

56:19.805 --> 56:23.332
Stop! Stop!

56:23.509 --> 56:27.309
Stop this unruly nonsense!

56:29.482 --> 56:31.950
Stop it right now!

56:33.185 --> 56:35.619
A little self-control, if you please!

56:35.788 --> 56:40.487
You bring this disorder, this aberration,
to the very heart of our community.

56:40.659 --> 56:41.921
Have you lost your minds?

56:42.094 --> 56:43.857
- We're just having fun.
- Harmless fun.

56:44.029 --> 56:48.261
"Harmless"? It is this kind of backsliding
that has brought the scarcity upon us.

56:48.434 --> 56:50.959
Excuse me, smiley. Can you speak
plain penguin, please?

56:51.137 --> 56:53.799
He thinks the food shortage
has something to do with me.

56:53.973 --> 56:57.637
Do you not understand that we can
only survive here when we're in harmony?

56:57.811 --> 57:01.042
When you and your foreign friends
lead us into your easy ways...

57:01.214 --> 57:02.841
...you offend the Great 'Guin.

57:03.016 --> 57:04.950
You invite him to withhold his bounty.

57:05.118 --> 57:08.713
- He rules the seasons.
- He giveth and he can taketh away.

57:08.889 --> 57:11.380
Wait a minute.
Happy feet can't cause a famine.

57:11.558 --> 57:15.153
If thy kind of pagan display
did not cause it, then what did?

57:15.328 --> 57:17.626
I think it comes from outside.
Way beyond the ice.

57:17.798 --> 57:20.130
There are things out there,
things we don't understand.

57:20.300 --> 57:21.961
- Mysteries.
- Mind-boggling mysteries.

57:22.135 --> 57:23.534
- Mystic beings.
- Yeah, aliens.

57:23.703 --> 57:25.330
- He's mad.
- No, aliens.

57:25.505 --> 57:27.166
- I hear they're smart.
- He's insane.

57:27.340 --> 57:29.968
No, they might be smarter than all of us.
Who knows?

57:30.143 --> 57:32.543
He drove the fish away,
now he's ranting this rubbish!

57:32.712 --> 57:35.977
- Hey, let me tell something to you.
- Don't touch me, you filthy vermin.

57:36.149 --> 57:37.980
- Hey, watch it.
- And so it follows.

57:38.151 --> 57:41.643
Dissent leads to division
and division leads us to doom.

57:41.822 --> 57:44.882
- You, Mumble Happy Feet, must go.
- Hear, hear.

57:45.058 --> 57:47.492
Don't you take one step, sweetheart.

57:47.661 --> 57:51.153
You have as much right to be here
as any of these daffy old fools.

57:51.998 --> 57:54.592
Norma Jean, I'll deal with this.

57:54.768 --> 57:56.235
Pa?

57:58.605 --> 58:01.597
Mumble, you must renounce
your so-called friends...

58:01.775 --> 58:03.800
...your peculiar thoughts,
your strange ways.

58:03.977 --> 58:05.342
- Memphis.
- If we are devout...

58:05.512 --> 58:07.639
...sincere in our praise,
the fish will return.

58:07.814 --> 58:11.079
- But, Pa...
- Listen, boy, I was a backslider myself.

58:11.251 --> 58:13.515
I was careless
and now we're paying the price.

58:13.687 --> 58:15.279
What's this got to do with Mumble?

58:15.455 --> 58:18.390
- It's why he is the way he is.
- There's nothing wrong with him!

58:18.558 --> 58:21.618
- Face it, our son's all messed up.
- He's not messed up, hear me?

58:21.795 --> 58:23.763
- Believe me, I know.
- How can you say that?

58:23.930 --> 58:27.024
Because when he was just an egg,
I dropped him!

58:27.200 --> 58:28.963
Memphis.

58:30.804 --> 58:32.362
Mumble.

58:34.674 --> 58:37.234
Oh, my poor little Mumble.

58:37.410 --> 58:39.071
But, Mom, I'm perfectly fine.

58:39.246 --> 58:41.237
- No. No, you're not, boy.
- That's right.

58:41.414 --> 58:44.975
For all our sakes, you must stop
this freakiness with the feet.

58:45.151 --> 58:49.281
Your father speaks wisely.
Heed his suffering heart and repent.

58:49.456 --> 58:51.651
But it just doesn't make any sense.

58:51.825 --> 58:53.884
Then your arrogance leaves us no choice!

58:54.060 --> 58:55.049
No, wait.

58:56.062 --> 59:00.328
Please, son, you can do this.
It ain't so hard.

59:02.269 --> 59:05.933
Don't ask me to change, Pa,
because I can't.

59:10.249 --> 59:14.151
And that, my brethren, is the end of it.

59:14.320 --> 59:16.220
You, begone!

59:19.158 --> 59:22.457
- Mumble.
- No, Ma, it's okay. It's okay.

59:23.696 --> 59:26.358
Let me tell something to you.

59:26.532 --> 59:28.659
When I find out
what's happening to the fish...

59:29.535 --> 59:31.332
...I'll be back.

59:32.171 --> 59:33.798
Let me through? Let me through.

59:33.973 --> 59:36.066
- Mumble, you don't have to go.
- Let it be.

59:36.242 --> 59:38.710
- Gloria.
- No. No, Dad, this isn't fair.

59:38.878 --> 59:41.108
Gloria, listen to your father.

59:41.614 --> 59:47.177
<i>My folks were always putting him down</i>

59:47.353 --> 59:50.220
<i>Down, down, down</i>

59:50.389 --> 59:54.655
<i>They said he came</i>
<i>From the wrong side of town</i>

59:54.827 --> 59:58.319
<i>He came from the wrong side of town</i>

59:58.498 --> 1:00:01.592
<i>They told me he was bad</i>

1:00:01.768 --> 1:00:02.860
<i>So bad</i>

1:00:03.035 --> 1:00:06.971
<i>- But I know he was sad</i>
<i>- So sad</i>

1:00:07.140 --> 1:00:12.305
<i>I'll never forget him</i>
<i>The leader of the pack</i>

1:00:12.478 --> 1:00:16.312
We sing the heart
of our true friend, Mumble.

1:00:16.482 --> 1:00:22.478
You are a nation of peeny-weeny,
piffling, <i>piccolini,</i> piddly-diddly pouft!

1:00:23.723 --> 1:00:25.623
Together, we prevail.

1:00:25.792 --> 1:00:27.657
In the wisdoms, we trust.

1:00:27.827 --> 1:00:29.761
We trust.

1:00:31.898 --> 1:00:34.731
<i>Look out</i>

1:00:34.901 --> 1:00:39.429
<i>Look out</i>

1:00:40.239 --> 1:00:43.208
<i>Look out</i>

1:00:43.376 --> 1:00:48.006
<i>Look</i>

1:00:48.181 --> 1:00:52.277
<i>Look out</i>

1:00:55.955 --> 1:01:00.153
Don't worry, tall guy.
My father also called me a pitiful loser.

1:01:00.326 --> 1:01:01.452
Look how I turn out.

1:01:01.627 --> 1:01:02.821
You're not helping, Ramon.

1:01:02.995 --> 1:01:06.692
He gonna be okay. All he gotta do
is find out what happened to the fish.

1:01:06.866 --> 1:01:08.834
- How he gonna do that?
- He think of something.

1:01:09.001 --> 1:01:10.992
- The aliens.
- What?

1:01:11.170 --> 1:01:14.004
- I'm gonna talk to the aliens.
- How you gonna find aliens?

1:01:14.174 --> 1:01:16.734
- Lovelace.
- He don't like you. He don't like you at all.

1:01:16.910 --> 1:01:19.003
That's okay. I'll appeal
to his better nature.

1:01:19.179 --> 1:01:21.647
- How you gonna do that?
- Cruel and unusual punishment?

1:01:21.815 --> 1:01:24.306
- Unimaginable torture?
- Imaginable torture?

1:01:24.484 --> 1:01:26.679
- Your singing?
- No!

1:01:26.854 --> 1:01:29.186
<i>"Can anybody find me"...</i>

1:01:29.590 --> 1:01:32.252
- You're cracking the ice!
- Avalanche!

1:01:32.426 --> 1:01:34.087
Yes, okay. Thank you.

1:01:44.504 --> 1:01:47.405
Lovelace. You there?

1:01:47.574 --> 1:01:49.701
Lovelace!

1:01:52.579 --> 1:01:54.376
Lovelace.

1:01:59.419 --> 1:02:01.046
Lovelace?

1:02:01.221 --> 1:02:02.552
Is this a bad time?

1:02:02.723 --> 1:02:04.657
I know we don't have
an appointment, but...

1:02:04.825 --> 1:02:06.952
Just one question and
I want a straight answer.

1:02:07.127 --> 1:02:08.719
Where do I find the mystic beings?

1:02:11.565 --> 1:02:13.556
Why don't he speak?

1:02:15.569 --> 1:02:18.197
Lovelace, you okay?

1:02:19.673 --> 1:02:22.870
- Boy, he's possessed.
- It's a seizure! It's a seizure!

1:02:23.043 --> 1:02:24.510
- Open the beak.
- Grab his tongue.

1:02:24.678 --> 1:02:27.272
He's choking. That thing
around his neck, it's too tight.

1:02:27.447 --> 1:02:30.075
- Well, why didn't you say so?
- On three.

1:02:30.250 --> 1:02:34.516
Stop! Listen! No! Amigos! Amigos! Stop!

1:02:34.688 --> 1:02:36.679
- What?
- You're hurting him.

1:02:38.759 --> 1:02:40.226
Any better?

1:02:40.394 --> 1:02:42.919
Lovelace, how did you get
that thing around your neck?

1:02:43.096 --> 1:02:46.429
- It was bestowed on him.
- By the mystic beings.

1:02:46.600 --> 1:02:48.761
- They didn't bestow it?
- No.

1:02:48.936 --> 1:02:51.928
Oh, come on, he don't know
what he's saying.

1:02:52.105 --> 1:02:55.097
You were swimming
and it just got caught around your neck.

1:02:55.275 --> 1:02:58.176
Oh, no way. He the guru.

1:02:59.179 --> 1:03:02.376
Lovelace, did you ever actually meet
a mystic being?

1:03:03.116 --> 1:03:04.743
Officially?

1:03:06.219 --> 1:03:07.208
No.

1:03:07.387 --> 1:03:09.321
I knew it! It's all a lie.

1:03:09.489 --> 1:03:11.354
But this belongs to someone.

1:03:11.525 --> 1:03:14.221
If we could find them,
I bet you they could take it off.

1:03:14.628 --> 1:03:18.861
Show me where you found it. I'm sure
they could help us. You and me both.

1:03:21.703 --> 1:03:23.603
Two words, three syllables.

1:03:23.771 --> 1:03:25.568
- What is it?
- You're dying?

1:03:25.740 --> 1:03:29.437
No, no, wait. Past, past, your past life.

1:03:29.610 --> 1:03:31.202
You're passing gas.

1:03:32.613 --> 1:03:34.604
Now he thinks he's an elephant seal.

1:03:34.782 --> 1:03:36.716
No, no, no. Go over the mountains.

1:03:36.884 --> 1:03:39.819
- Go over the mountains!
- Through the land of the elephant seals.

1:03:39.988 --> 1:03:44.584
- Beyond the land of the elephant seals.
- Beyond the land of the elephant seals!

1:03:55.536 --> 1:03:57.697
- Wait.
- What?

1:03:58.606 --> 1:04:00.597
I hear voices.

1:04:00.775 --> 1:04:02.436
- There is a voice.
- Where?

1:04:02.610 --> 1:04:06.171
- There's a little voice on the wind.
- Mumble!

1:04:06.347 --> 1:04:07.644
- "Mambo"?
- "Mambo"?

1:04:07.815 --> 1:04:09.248
- Listen.
- Mumble Happy Feet.

1:04:09.784 --> 1:04:11.012
- Gloria?
- Gloria!

1:04:11.185 --> 1:04:12.174
Gloria?

1:04:12.353 --> 1:04:14.878
Hey, you got a stalker.
She's obsessed with you, man.

1:04:18.493 --> 1:04:20.961
I can't believe it's you.

1:04:21.129 --> 1:04:23.188
Of course it's me.

1:04:24.499 --> 1:04:26.194
What are you doing here?

1:04:26.367 --> 1:04:29.564
<i>All the love in the world can't be gone</i>

1:04:29.737 --> 1:04:33.605
<i>All the need to be loved can't be wrong</i>

1:04:33.775 --> 1:04:36.505
- Oh, my.
- So which way, twinkletoes?

1:04:36.677 --> 1:04:40.044
No, no, no. If you come,
you may never get back home.

1:04:40.214 --> 1:04:41.579
Fine by me.

1:04:41.749 --> 1:04:47.210
Gloria, you have a life back there.
I don't. I mean, we don't. Not out here.

1:04:47.388 --> 1:04:50.482
How can we keep an egg safe?
That's if we ever had an egg.

1:04:50.658 --> 1:04:53.252
Well, I don't need an egg to be happy.

1:04:53.428 --> 1:04:57.455
You say that now, but what about later
when all your friends have eggs?

1:04:58.833 --> 1:05:00.061
Then I'll have you.

1:05:01.502 --> 1:05:04.903
Now he's going to pledge
his soul forever.

1:05:05.073 --> 1:05:06.199
- Gloria.
- Here it comes.

1:05:06.374 --> 1:05:13.303
I'm a particular kind of guy,
the kind of guy who needs his own space.

1:05:13.581 --> 1:05:15.446
It's not you, it's me.

1:05:15.616 --> 1:05:18.050
I'm just not up for a serious relationship
right now.

1:05:18.219 --> 1:05:21.552
What he's trying to do now
is he's pushing her away. Let's watch.

1:05:21.722 --> 1:05:25.214
No matter what you say or do,
you're stuck with me.

1:05:25.393 --> 1:05:28.488
Oh, come on. As if you're not
totally thrilled that I'm here.

1:05:28.664 --> 1:05:32.122
- Now she got him on the ropes.
- See, right there is your problem.

1:05:32.301 --> 1:05:34.201
You think you're irresistible, don't you?

1:05:34.369 --> 1:05:36.701
I don't care where you're from,
that's got to hurt.

1:05:36.872 --> 1:05:39.602
- Excuse me?
- Gloria's so gorgeous, Gloria's so talented.

1:05:39.775 --> 1:05:40.764
What?

1:05:40.943 --> 1:05:43.343
Just because
you can hit a few high notes.

1:05:43.512 --> 1:05:45.639
You got a problem with my singing?

1:05:45.814 --> 1:05:48.044
No, it's perfectly fine.

1:05:48.217 --> 1:05:50.082
- "Fine"?
- If you like that sort of thing.

1:05:50.252 --> 1:05:52.846
- It's a little Nana Tootsie for my taste.
- What?

1:05:53.021 --> 1:05:55.148
You know, showy, flashy, froufrou.

1:05:55.324 --> 1:05:56.814
- "Froufrou"?
- That's right.

1:05:56.992 --> 1:06:01.122
Coming from someone who thinks it's cool
to jig up and down really fast on the spot...

1:06:01.296 --> 1:06:03.560
...like some twitchy idiot.

1:06:07.336 --> 1:06:09.964
You stubborn, hippity-hoppity fool!

1:06:10.139 --> 1:06:12.004
Right back at you.

1:06:22.351 --> 1:06:24.842
Amigo, that was a good thing you do.

1:06:25.020 --> 1:06:27.284
She is going to be so much better off
without you.

1:06:27.456 --> 1:06:30.584
She is going to find a good, steady guy
to comfort her...

1:06:30.759 --> 1:06:33.956
...and love her up real good
and raise a big family.

1:06:34.129 --> 1:06:36.359
- Ramon.
- And then she's going to let herself go...

1:06:36.532 --> 1:06:39.660
Ramon. He's hurting. He's hurting bad.

1:06:39.835 --> 1:06:44.499
Oh, listen, listen, don't hold it in
or you explode. You got to let it out.

1:06:44.673 --> 1:06:47.369
You just let it out. You let it out.

1:06:47.543 --> 1:06:50.410
Everybody, turn away for a moment.

1:06:50.579 --> 1:06:52.877
<i>If she leave him now</i>

1:06:53.048 --> 1:06:58.247
<i>She take away the biggest part of him</i>

1:07:00.622 --> 1:07:02.556
<i>Don't, baby, please, don't go</i>

1:07:02.724 --> 1:07:04.589
Please, guys.

1:07:04.760 --> 1:07:06.751
No more singing.

1:07:17.339 --> 1:07:20.001
Then she say to me, "Enough,
you are making me nauseous."

1:07:20.175 --> 1:07:23.906
So I become silent, almost moody,
and you know what she says?

1:07:24.079 --> 1:07:26.138
"You never share. You got to let it out."

1:07:26.315 --> 1:07:29.079
- Ramon, come on.
- Let it out. Let it out.

1:07:29.251 --> 1:07:30.684
Stop it! Let it go.

1:07:30.852 --> 1:07:34.516
- I never had a good relationship in my life.
- Give him a hug. Give him a hug.

1:07:34.691 --> 1:07:35.919
- I let it out!
- There we go.

1:07:36.092 --> 1:07:38.652
- I let it out.
- I know. Get over it.

1:07:38.828 --> 1:07:41.626
- Can you keep going?
- Yeah.

1:07:41.798 --> 1:07:44.995
- What's that smell?
- It wasn't me.

1:07:46.135 --> 1:07:49.901
Hey, Fluffy, we're following you.
Get up here.

1:07:58.047 --> 1:08:02.108
So these elephant seals,
they're not penguin eaters, are they?

1:08:02.285 --> 1:08:04.685
I don't know.
I believe they are herbivores.

1:08:04.854 --> 1:08:06.719
- What?
- You know, kelp-suckers.

1:08:06.889 --> 1:08:09.221
Here we go, Lovelace. Come on.

1:08:10.893 --> 1:08:12.758
Jump in time. Jump in time.

1:08:12.929 --> 1:08:15.693
- Okay, let's do it.
- Okay, okay, okay. Ready?

1:08:18.901 --> 1:08:21.301
I can do this. I can do this.
I got to trick myself.

1:08:21.471 --> 1:08:23.371
Boy, look at that. What?

1:08:39.322 --> 1:08:43.884
You blokes better be lost,
because trespassing's a crime.

1:08:44.060 --> 1:08:48.053
- We're just passing through.
- Yeah. We're with him.

1:08:48.665 --> 1:08:51.133
You wouldn't be heading
over them distant hills...

1:08:51.301 --> 1:08:53.235
...and through the blizzard country?

1:08:53.403 --> 1:08:56.201
If it's the only way
to the forbidden shore, yeah.

1:08:56.372 --> 1:08:57.566
Crikey.

1:08:57.740 --> 1:09:01.232
You might come face to face
with an annihilator.

1:09:01.411 --> 1:09:02.435
An alien annihilator?

1:09:02.612 --> 1:09:05.547
Too right. Cut you up
as soon as look at you.

1:09:05.715 --> 1:09:08.741
Waste every living thing in their path.

1:09:08.918 --> 1:09:10.579
Could they be annihilating the fish?

1:09:10.753 --> 1:09:12.345
Every living thing.

1:09:12.522 --> 1:09:14.990
Merciless, mate. Merciless.

1:09:15.158 --> 1:09:17.456
Even if you're a whopping great whale...

1:09:17.627 --> 1:09:20.289
...they drag your sorry carcass ashore...

1:09:20.463 --> 1:09:26.163
...dice you up, melt you down,
and turn you into fun food.

1:09:26.336 --> 1:09:28.600
One day you're a big old whale...

1:09:28.771 --> 1:09:31.069
...next minute...

1:09:31.240 --> 1:09:32.639
...fun food.

1:09:32.809 --> 1:09:34.242
Someone's gotta stop them.

1:09:34.410 --> 1:09:36.901
Oh, yeah? What's gonna be
your approach?

1:09:37.080 --> 1:09:39.105
If I could just talk to them.

1:09:39.282 --> 1:09:40.773
Appeal to their better nature.

1:09:40.951 --> 1:09:41.940
Beauty.

1:09:42.119 --> 1:09:47.716
When that crafty little trick pays off,
you be sure to let us know, won't you?

1:09:47.891 --> 1:09:50.758
All right, Lovelace, let's go.

1:09:52.996 --> 1:09:55.089
See you, Lovelace.

1:09:57.534 --> 1:09:59.968
Your funeral, mate.

1:10:47.785 --> 1:10:50.345
Oh, man!

1:10:51.388 --> 1:10:54.118
- Push tight.
- Okay.

1:11:08.772 --> 1:11:10.933
Come on, guys. Let's do it.

1:11:11.108 --> 1:11:15.010
You can do it. Come on, push!

1:11:59.257 --> 1:12:01.282
What's that noise?

1:12:02.827 --> 1:12:04.021
There's no noise.

1:12:04.195 --> 1:12:06.755
- No gasping. No wheezing.
- Where's Lovelace?

1:12:08.833 --> 1:12:13.600
Sometimes a brave penguin
will just slip away to die.

1:12:13.771 --> 1:12:15.705
Do you think he went to a happy place?

1:12:15.874 --> 1:12:19.469
- Probably.
- No, no. I think he went this way.

1:12:31.523 --> 1:12:34.014
Come on. Let's go.

1:12:50.608 --> 1:12:52.508
Lovelace!

1:12:53.678 --> 1:12:56.169
Lovelace!

1:13:02.220 --> 1:13:04.051
Hello?

1:13:05.456 --> 1:13:06.855
Is there anyone there?

1:13:07.025 --> 1:13:10.620
- No... No need to shout.
- Somebody might hear you.

1:13:16.267 --> 1:13:18.030
His feet don't look too good.

1:13:18.202 --> 1:13:20.796
- He rested here.
- Now he's on his belly!

1:13:20.972 --> 1:13:23.532
- No, this way.
- You don't want to know what he did here.

1:13:23.708 --> 1:13:25.938
- You're right.
- There he is. Lovelace!

1:13:26.110 --> 1:13:29.409
- All right! Lovelace!
- Lovelace!

1:13:32.183 --> 1:13:33.946
- Oh, look at Lovelace.
- We're here.

1:13:34.118 --> 1:13:37.679
- Are you okay?
- Come on, man. Hang in there, buddy.

1:13:38.556 --> 1:13:40.183
What is it?

1:13:40.358 --> 1:13:43.623
Oh, look. There's one for everyone.

1:13:43.795 --> 1:13:46.320
Hang in there, Lovelace.
I know they're here somewhere.

1:13:46.497 --> 1:13:49.022
- Why would they leave all this behind?
- I don't know.

1:13:50.034 --> 1:13:51.023
Hey.

1:13:51.202 --> 1:13:53.466
- Tell them we come in peace.
- We come in peace!

1:13:53.638 --> 1:13:55.162
- Lovelace.
- Lovelace.

1:13:55.341 --> 1:13:56.808
- Lovelace.
- Oh, buddy, come on.

1:13:56.976 --> 1:13:59.035
- Are you okay?
- Hang in there, buddy.

1:14:01.647 --> 1:14:04.115
- Oh, that's not good.
- Stay calm.

1:14:04.283 --> 1:14:05.580
- Stay calm.
- That's not good.

1:14:05.751 --> 1:14:08.345
- Okay, don't stay calm!
- Panic!

1:14:15.060 --> 1:14:17.028
Oh, no, no!

1:14:19.064 --> 1:14:22.158
- Oh, they're making us appe-teasers.
- They're appe-teasing us!

1:14:22.334 --> 1:14:24.461
We're all gonna die.

1:14:25.738 --> 1:14:27.603
Whatever you do, stay out of the water!

1:14:27.773 --> 1:14:29.900
- Stay out of the water.
- Don't go in the water!

1:14:30.075 --> 1:14:32.771
Lovelace, don't go in the water!

1:14:38.617 --> 1:14:40.141
Lovelace, hang in there!

1:14:40.319 --> 1:14:42.219
Hang in there!

1:14:43.589 --> 1:14:46.581
Get your dirty tongue off him!

1:14:48.994 --> 1:14:50.894
No, no, no!

1:14:51.063 --> 1:14:52.530
Stay out of the water!

1:14:52.698 --> 1:14:54.393
- Mumble!
- Mumble!

1:15:24.663 --> 1:15:29.259
- They playing birdminton?
- No, it's a show. Dinner and a show.

1:15:32.905 --> 1:15:35.465
Lovelace!

1:15:40.979 --> 1:15:42.970
Rejoice!

1:15:51.390 --> 1:15:52.584
Lovelace!

1:15:52.758 --> 1:15:54.817
- Help!
- Reach out!

1:15:54.993 --> 1:15:56.824
Thank you, my brother, thank you!

1:16:07.807 --> 1:16:09.672
I wasn't scared! I wasn't scared!

1:16:10.477 --> 1:16:14.413
Oh, my beautiful brother, thank you,
thank you, thank you, thank you!

1:16:18.585 --> 1:16:21.554
- Go, Lovelace! You the man!
- Go, go, go, go, go!

1:16:21.721 --> 1:16:24.189
Enough!

1:16:24.357 --> 1:16:26.450
It's a bad day for you!

1:16:26.626 --> 1:16:28.685
You dealing with Lovelace now!

1:16:28.862 --> 1:16:31.524
- And my man, Mumble, here.
- You tell them, Lovelace.

1:16:31.698 --> 1:16:34.462
Begone, demon fish. Adios.

1:16:35.869 --> 1:16:37.496
That's right.

1:16:37.670 --> 1:16:39.433
You hightail it back to your mamas.

1:16:39.739 --> 1:16:41.798
- How did he do that?
- Don't make me come in the water.

1:16:41.975 --> 1:16:43.909
I'll come after your sons and daughters.

1:16:44.077 --> 1:16:46.068
I'm gonna give you the bad eye.

1:17:40.366 --> 1:17:41.697
A whole bunch of them.

1:17:41.868 --> 1:17:44.496
They gonna rule the world.

1:17:44.671 --> 1:17:45.660
It's gotta be them.

1:17:45.839 --> 1:17:49.104
- If it is, I don't wanna know about it.
- They don't even know we exist.

1:17:49.275 --> 1:17:50.606
Let me tell something to you.

1:17:50.777 --> 1:17:53.769
This is the end of the road. It's over.

1:17:53.947 --> 1:17:56.848
You did everything penguinly possible.

1:17:57.016 --> 1:17:59.484
- You found the aliens.
- We gonna testify to that.

1:17:59.652 --> 1:18:03.019
We'll tell your whole laughing-boy nation
they were dead wrong about you.

1:18:03.189 --> 1:18:04.986
Now, let's all go back home. Right now.

1:18:05.158 --> 1:18:06.523
Right on.

1:18:06.693 --> 1:18:08.285
- Could I ask a favor of you?
- Sure.

1:18:08.461 --> 1:18:11.022
- What kind of favor?
- Could you make sure Gloria's okay?

1:18:11.198 --> 1:18:12.563
- And my ma.
- What?

1:18:12.733 --> 1:18:14.325
And if you see Pa...

1:18:14.501 --> 1:18:17.368
...tell him I tried.

1:18:17.538 --> 1:18:19.028
Okay, what you talking about?

1:18:19.206 --> 1:18:20.969
I'm gonna stop them taking our fish.

1:18:21.141 --> 1:18:22.699
How you gonna do that, Mumble?

1:18:25.079 --> 1:18:28.139
Adios, amigos!

1:18:28.482 --> 1:18:29.972
Amigo! He did it.

1:18:53.540 --> 1:18:54.564
You believe that?

1:18:54.742 --> 1:18:58.303
How we gonna tell his mama
he bring us all this way just to kill himself?

1:18:58.479 --> 1:19:01.243
No. He didn't. Look.

1:19:02.082 --> 1:19:03.845
He loco maniac.

1:19:04.018 --> 1:19:06.953
First ever flying flipper bird.

1:19:07.121 --> 1:19:09.282
How tall you think that tall boy was?

1:19:09.456 --> 1:19:12.619
Who could say? Taller than anyone.

1:19:12.793 --> 1:19:16.729
Hey, it's me, Lovelace...

1:19:16.897 --> 1:19:19.297
...formerly known as "guru."

1:19:19.466 --> 1:19:22.458
I'm gonna be telling your story,
Happy Feet...

1:19:22.636 --> 1:19:26.504
...long after you dead and gone!

1:19:43.524 --> 1:19:45.788
Hey! Hey!

1:20:35.944 --> 1:20:38.640
<i>Enraged by their indifference...</i>

1:20:38.813 --> 1:20:44.149
<i>... he followed them long after</i>
<i>they were gone from his sight.</i>

1:20:46.321 --> 1:20:50.553
<i>He ventured further</i>
<i>than any of us had gone before...</i>

1:20:50.725 --> 1:20:54.559
<i>... beyond all hope of return.</i>

1:20:55.497 --> 1:20:57.931
<i>Swept up by the great currents...</i>

1:20:58.099 --> 1:21:02.763
<i>... he was carried endlessly</i>
<i>across vast oceans...</i>

1:21:02.937 --> 1:21:06.634
<i>... to worlds unknown.</i>

1:22:02.931 --> 1:22:05.695
Excuse me. What is this place?

1:22:05.867 --> 1:22:08.859
You're in heaven, Dave. Penguin heaven.

1:22:09.037 --> 1:22:11.028
Is it anywhere near Emperor Land?

1:22:11.206 --> 1:22:14.004
It's wherever you want it to be.

1:22:14.843 --> 1:22:18.870
Try the water, Dave. It's really real.

1:22:34.964 --> 1:22:39.333
<i>I heard tell,</i>
<i>when he finally saw aliens up close...</i>

1:22:39.502 --> 1:22:43.700
<i>... they were just as the skua</i>
<i>had described.</i>

1:22:43.873 --> 1:22:46.501
Excuse me. Why are you taking our fish?

1:22:46.675 --> 1:22:51.977
<i>Big, ugly penguins without feathers</i>
<i>on their fat, flabby faces.</i>

1:22:52.148 --> 1:22:57.882
Why are you taking our fish?
You're kind of killing us out there.

1:23:00.256 --> 1:23:02.349
No! No, wait!

1:23:11.967 --> 1:23:13.935
Oh, my.

1:23:15.004 --> 1:23:19.168
Hello. Hello from Emperor Land.
Good afternoon.

1:23:19.341 --> 1:23:21.104
Why are you taking our fish?

1:23:21.277 --> 1:23:25.714
I'm sure you don't mean to,
but you're causing an awful lot of grief.

1:23:26.715 --> 1:23:30.708
Am I not making myself clear?
I'm speaking plain penguin.

1:23:31.620 --> 1:23:35.181
Penguin! Don't you understand?
You're stealing our fish.

1:23:39.461 --> 1:23:42.191
Oh, please, anyone, talk to me!

1:23:42.364 --> 1:23:44.594
For pity's sake, you're stealing our F-l-S...

1:23:49.371 --> 1:23:54.138
<i>After three days, he would lose his voice.</i>

1:23:54.310 --> 1:23:56.744
<i>After three months...</i>

1:23:58.714 --> 1:24:02.844
<i>... he would all but lose his mind.</i>

1:24:15.264 --> 1:24:18.233
So you found the fish, baby.

1:24:19.335 --> 1:24:20.996
Ma?

1:24:21.170 --> 1:24:22.467
- Hi, sweetie.
- Ma.

1:24:22.638 --> 1:24:27.041
Fluffy, no matter what they say or do,
we never stopped believing in you.

1:24:27.209 --> 1:24:29.302
So you'll be back soon, right?

1:24:29.478 --> 1:24:31.105
Hey, come on. Let him eat.

1:24:31.280 --> 1:24:33.272
Go ahead, Dave. Don't mind us.

1:24:33.783 --> 1:24:35.250
But there's plenty for everyone.

1:24:35.418 --> 1:24:37.716
It's okay, sugar. We can wait.

1:24:37.887 --> 1:24:39.718
No, no, Ma! Ma!

1:24:39.889 --> 1:24:43.290
There's lots here. Ma!

1:24:47.230 --> 1:24:48.822
Ma!

1:27:09.039 --> 1:27:11.735
- Kids, you gotta see this.
- He's on now.

1:27:33.497 --> 1:27:35.863
Hey! Hello!

1:27:38.302 --> 1:27:40.862
- Isn't that the fellow with the wacky feet?
- Looks like.

1:27:41.038 --> 1:27:43.336
- What was his name?
- I thought he was dead.

1:27:43.507 --> 1:27:44.906
- Everybody...
- Apparently not.

1:27:45.075 --> 1:27:48.010
Everybody, listen up! I've got big news.

1:27:48.345 --> 1:27:50.336
I know who's taking the fish!

1:27:50.514 --> 1:27:52.982
- Yeah, and they took his brain.
- It's the aliens.

1:27:53.150 --> 1:27:55.414
- I made contact with them.
- The lunatic is back.

1:27:55.586 --> 1:27:57.577
The aliens are taking our fish.

1:27:57.755 --> 1:27:59.814
Someone ought to fetch
Noah and the elders.

1:27:59.990 --> 1:28:01.287
Hey, you.

1:28:01.859 --> 1:28:03.417
Gloria.

1:28:03.594 --> 1:28:05.687
Kind of weird, seeing you again.

1:28:06.197 --> 1:28:07.186
Yeah.

1:28:07.364 --> 1:28:09.730
- Everything cool here, baby?
- You remember Seymour.

1:28:09.900 --> 1:28:11.197
Yeah. Hi, Seymour.

1:28:11.368 --> 1:28:12.858
Yeah.

1:28:14.171 --> 1:28:15.900
So which one is yours?

1:28:17.141 --> 1:28:18.403
All of them.

1:28:20.778 --> 1:28:24.908
This is our singing class.
He teaches rhythm. I teach the blues.

1:28:25.082 --> 1:28:27.676
- So you're not...?
- I guess I never heard the right song.

1:28:27.852 --> 1:28:30.980
That's great! I didn't mean...

1:28:31.322 --> 1:28:32.914
I found out who's taking the fish.

1:28:33.090 --> 1:28:35.217
They're big and kind of ugly,
but, Gloria...

1:28:35.392 --> 1:28:37.690
...the things they can do.
They're coming here.

1:28:37.862 --> 1:28:38.988
Oh, is that so?

1:28:39.163 --> 1:28:41.563
They'll be here soon.
I think they wanna help us.

1:28:41.732 --> 1:28:43.461
So now you speak with them?

1:28:43.634 --> 1:28:46.832
Well, they don't speak penguin,
but they seem to respond to this.

1:28:47.005 --> 1:28:49.064
- What's he doing?
- You gotta be kidding me.

1:28:49.241 --> 1:28:52.267
I suggest we all do it.
It really gets their attention.

1:28:52.444 --> 1:28:53.775
And why would it do that?

1:28:53.945 --> 1:28:56.846
Beats me, but it works.

1:28:57.015 --> 1:28:59.882
- Hey, it's the hippity-hopper.
- Freaky feet!

1:29:00.051 --> 1:29:01.040
Boys, boys...

1:29:01.219 --> 1:29:02.208
- Fluffy.
- Tall guy.

1:29:02.387 --> 1:29:04.378
- Stretch!
- Amigo!

1:29:07.993 --> 1:29:10.860
So you dare come back?

1:29:11.162 --> 1:29:13.756
He says he's found aliens
and they're taking our fish.

1:29:13.932 --> 1:29:16.457
He says that they're coming
and we all have to do this.

1:29:17.936 --> 1:29:21.463
There be no such thing as aliens!

1:29:23.575 --> 1:29:26.305
Mumble, turn around.

1:29:29.447 --> 1:29:30.937
It's a disease.

1:29:31.349 --> 1:29:33.044
Is that from them?

1:29:33.752 --> 1:29:37.916
Yeah. But don't be afraid.
I think it's a way to find me, that's all.

1:29:38.089 --> 1:29:41.786
You led them here?
You turned them on your own kind?

1:29:42.594 --> 1:29:46.496
Wait a second, you just said
there's no such thing as aliens.

1:29:48.934 --> 1:29:51.061
Well, there's not.

1:29:51.236 --> 1:29:54.865
But if there were, only a traitorous fool
would bring them here.

1:29:55.040 --> 1:29:56.132
But they have to come.

1:29:56.308 --> 1:29:59.277
They're the ones taking our fish.
They can do something about it.

1:29:59.444 --> 1:30:02.936
None but the Great 'Guin
has the power to give and take away.

1:30:03.114 --> 1:30:07.574
The Great 'Guin didn't put things
out of whack, the aliens did.

1:30:08.153 --> 1:30:12.089
A fool returns this day
to mock our suffering.

1:30:12.257 --> 1:30:16.387
We are starving
and he wants us to hippity-hop.

1:30:16.561 --> 1:30:19.496
So do we hold fast to our ways...

1:30:19.664 --> 1:30:24.363
...or do we bend to the fetid fantasies
of a dancing fool?

1:30:33.178 --> 1:30:35.874
Say, how does that feet thing go again?

1:30:36.047 --> 1:30:37.605
Yeah, show us, Mumble.

1:30:38.984 --> 1:30:41.043
Oh, it's really quite easy.

1:30:41.219 --> 1:30:42.846
No, no!

1:30:43.021 --> 1:30:44.352
No, you must resist!

1:30:45.190 --> 1:30:46.885
That's right.

1:30:47.258 --> 1:30:50.625
- Pointless nonsense.
- Resist! Stand your ground!

1:30:50.795 --> 1:30:54.129
Stand your ground against this folly!

1:30:59.905 --> 1:31:02.965
Raise your voices, brothers.

1:31:03.142 --> 1:31:06.441
Cry out in defiance of this jiggity-joggity!

1:31:06.612 --> 1:31:08.739
Show me what you got.

1:31:11.550 --> 1:31:13.279
You got it.

1:31:17.823 --> 1:31:19.256
Come on.

1:31:19.425 --> 1:31:20.756
Work, work it.

1:31:20.926 --> 1:31:24.020
Yes, yes! Call on the wisdoms!

1:31:24.196 --> 1:31:25.925
Let the world tremble!

1:31:26.365 --> 1:31:28.230
For when all others leave...

1:31:28.401 --> 1:31:30.266
...we remain!

1:31:32.004 --> 1:31:33.631
Mumble! Mumble!

1:31:33.806 --> 1:31:36.604
Mama? Amigos.

1:31:37.977 --> 1:31:40.810
- Oh, Mama.
- Oh, my boy.

1:31:40.980 --> 1:31:43.574
- My gorgeous boy.
- Oh, Mama.

1:31:43.749 --> 1:31:45.876
- Look at him.
- You're so dazzling.

1:31:46.052 --> 1:31:48.919
- Oh, Fluffy.
- We waited and waited for you.

1:31:49.088 --> 1:31:51.921
- Oh, yeah.
- Where's Pa?

1:31:52.091 --> 1:31:54.355
Believe me. You don't wanna see
your deadbeat dad.

1:31:54.527 --> 1:31:56.586
- Your pa is sort of...
- What?

1:31:56.762 --> 1:31:59.060
Come on, I'll show you.

1:32:08.441 --> 1:32:10.238
Memphis?

1:32:11.277 --> 1:32:12.710
Memphis?

1:32:12.878 --> 1:32:14.368
Pa?

1:32:18.284 --> 1:32:19.911
Mumble?

1:32:20.086 --> 1:32:22.077
Is it truly you?

1:32:22.254 --> 1:32:24.586
Every last bit of me, Pa.

1:32:28.761 --> 1:32:30.592
I thought...

1:32:34.734 --> 1:32:36.224
Pa?

1:32:39.839 --> 1:32:42.239
There ain't been one day...

1:32:44.210 --> 1:32:48.840
...not one day, that I done right by you.

1:32:53.185 --> 1:32:55.210
Oh, Pa.

1:32:55.387 --> 1:32:57.252
Dance for him, Daddy.

1:32:57.423 --> 1:32:59.414
Dance with your boy.

1:33:02.763 --> 1:33:05.163
You'll have to forgive me.

1:33:05.966 --> 1:33:09.026
The music's gone clean out of me.

1:33:10.904 --> 1:33:12.496
No, it hasn't.

1:33:12.672 --> 1:33:16.472
It's just like singing with your body.

1:33:16.643 --> 1:33:18.668
Come on, baby. We can do it.

1:33:18.845 --> 1:33:20.403
Oh, Mama.

1:33:20.580 --> 1:33:24.949
It's just one big old foot after the other.

1:33:30.357 --> 1:33:31.346
That's it.

1:33:33.360 --> 1:33:35.191
Yeah.

1:33:36.563 --> 1:33:39.396
- Yeah, see?
- Well, that feels good.

1:33:44.638 --> 1:33:48.074
<i>You don't have to be beautiful</i>

1:33:48.508 --> 1:33:49.497
Yeah, Memphis.

1:33:49.743 --> 1:33:51.370
<i>To turn me on</i>

1:33:51.845 --> 1:33:52.834
Daddy.

1:33:53.013 --> 1:33:57.040
<i>I just need your body, baby</i>

1:33:57.217 --> 1:33:59.708
<i>From dusk till dawn</i>

1:34:00.921 --> 1:34:04.652
<i>You don't have to be rich to be my girl</i>

1:34:04.825 --> 1:34:08.818
<i>You don't have to be cool</i>
<i>To rule my world</i>

1:34:08.951 --> 1:34:12.853
<i>Ain't no particular song</i>
<i>I'm more compatible with</i>

1:34:13.022 --> 1:34:17.686
<i>I just want your extra time and your...</i>

1:34:38.014 --> 1:34:41.040
Holy flock!

1:35:06.442 --> 1:35:08.876
Mommy, Mommy, Mommy.

1:35:45.548 --> 1:35:47.914
I think you better dance now.

1:36:41.470 --> 1:36:43.938
First, there was just one.
Now there's thousands.

1:36:44.106 --> 1:36:46.802
- Are they trying to tell us something?
- What's the problem?

1:36:46.976 --> 1:36:49.774
- We're messing with their food chain.
- We've gotta do something.

1:36:49.946 --> 1:36:53.643
- We suggest a ban on all marine harvesting.
- Too much money. Too many jobs.

1:36:55.551 --> 1:36:57.712
Why should we do anything at all?

1:37:03.426 --> 1:37:06.793
They're just a bunch of flightless birds
at the bottom of the world.

1:37:11.300 --> 1:37:13.632
I don't wanna live in a world
without penguins.

1:37:13.803 --> 1:37:15.168
What are we gonna do about it?

1:37:15.338 --> 1:37:16.999
Bang up the sign "No Fishing."

1:37:18.774 --> 1:37:22.175
Is equal to the love...

1:37:22.345 --> 1:37:23.744
...you make.

1:37:27.817 --> 1:37:31.981
<i>Oh, baby. Right on.</i>

1:37:44.500 --> 1:37:49.631
<i>Looking back on when I</i>
<i>Was a little nappy-headed boy</i>

1:37:52.475 --> 1:37:53.942
<i>It's like a jungle sometimes</i>

1:37:54.110 --> 1:37:56.305
<i>It makes me wonder</i>
<i>How I keep from going under</i>

1:37:58.247 --> 1:37:59.714
Bring it on! Go ahead!

1:38:00.583 --> 1:38:04.576
<i>Even though we sometimes</i>
<i>Would not get a thing</i>

1:38:04.754 --> 1:38:08.622
<i>We were happy with</i>
<i>The joy the day would bring</i>

1:38:08.791 --> 1:38:11.954
<i>I wish those days</i>
<i>Would come back once more</i>

1:38:12.128 --> 1:38:16.326
<i>Come back those days, those days</i>
<i>Come back, don't go</i>

1:38:16.732 --> 1:38:19.394
Come here, babe. Come on back.

1:38:19.568 --> 1:38:20.557
<i>Come on back</i>

1:38:20.736 --> 1:38:22.363
<i>- Come on back</i>
<i>- Come on back</i>

1:38:22.538 --> 1:38:25.029
<i>- Come on back</i>
<i>- Come on back</i>

1:38:25.207 --> 1:38:27.402
<i>I love them, I love them</i>

1:38:27.576 --> 1:38:28.736
<i>I love them, I love them</i>

1:38:33.549 --> 1:38:36.677
<i>Those days, those days</i>
<i>Those days, those days</i>

1:38:36.852 --> 1:38:42.347
<i>Those days</i>

